The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 23: Pune-based Kalyani Steels has entered into a joint venture with Brazils Gerdau to enhance the capacity of SJK Steel Plant, a company it has acquired recently. Through the venture, Kalyani Steels will increase its capacity to 1.6 million tonnes per annum of finished steel in the next few years. Under the agreement, both companies will have an equity partnership of 45 per cent each in SJK Steel.

 Islamabad, June 23: Pakistan will raise $650.3 million through the sale of a 25 per cent stake in the United Bank, the countrys third-largest bank, through an issue of global depositary receipts. The GDRs, to be listed on the London Stock Exchange, will be offered at $12.85 each.

 Bhubaneswar, June 23: The State Bank of India has sought the RBIs permission to open 40 branches in Orissa. The bank also plans to extend core banking solution to all its 502 branches this fiscal. The SBI has 249 ATMs in the state.

 London/Milan, June 23: The London Stock Exchange will buy an Italian bourse for 1.6 billion euros ($2.15 billion). The bourses said they planned to become the worlds capital market and that together they accounted for 48 per cent of the FTSE Eurofirst 100 index of companies by market value.




